01:20:11,446 --> 01:20:15,030
Say that doctor you
mentioned... erm, Gluckstein.

963
01:20:15,868 --> 01:20:19,998
Would your records be able to tell
us where he ended up, for instance?

964
01:20:22,085 --> 01:20:24,755
- We need to check a record.
- Yes, sir.

965
01:20:27,133 --> 01:20:28,544
Gluckstein.

966
01:20:29,553 --> 01:20:33,089
The full name's... Maurice Israel.

967
01:20:38,356 --> 01:20:41,062
- Year of birth?
- 1899.

968
01:20:44,322 --> 01:20:46,066
Or thereabouts.

969
01:20:48,076 --> 01:20:52,539
Well, I wish I could wait and see
the outcome of our little experiment,

970
01:20:52,583 --> 01:20:56,534
but you wouldn't believe the paperwork
that ends up on my desk. Good luck.

971
01:20:56,588 --> 01:20:58,297
Thank you, sir.

972
01:21:11,399 --> 01:21:13,475
Gluckstein, M.I.

973
01:21:15,154 --> 01:21:17,230
Evacuated to Silesia.

974
01:21:18,742 --> 01:21:20,984
Does it say when he was picked up?

975
01:21:35,931 --> 01:21:37,390
Thank you.

976
01:21:51,868 --> 01:21:53,778
Aren't you going to say goodbye?

977
01:21:55,874 --> 01:21:59,539
- I know what you did.
- What are you talking about?

978
01:21:59,586 --> 01:22:02,375
- He came to the house that night.
- Who?

979
01:22:04,635 --> 01:22:06,711
You turned him in.

980
01:22:08,599 --> 01:22:10,675
How can you think that?

981
01:22:13,981 --> 01:22:19,522
One thing you can say for the Gestapo,
they keep extremely thorough records.

982
01:22:21,031 --> 01:22:22,230
Drive on.

983
01:22:22,283 --> 01:22:25,653
Oh, John... John! Please!

984
01:22:25,704 --> 01:22:26,903
Please!

985
01:23:18,064 --> 01:23:19,523
Heil Hitler.

986
01:23:20,734 --> 01:23:23,688
- Heil Hitler.
- Hauptsturmführer Halder?

987
01:23:25,574 --> 01:23:27,448
I prefer "Professor".

988
01:23:28,494 --> 01:23:30,451
Step this way, Professor.

989
01:23:31,164 --> 01:23:33,038
Thank you.

990
01:23:33,083 --> 01:23:35,290
I trust you'll find everything in order.

991
01:23:36,128 --> 01:23:39,712
Obersturmbannführer Eichmann
will be pleased to hear it.

992
01:23:39,758 --> 01:23:43,924
In fact, he asked me to
carry out a little experiment.

993
01:23:45,474 --> 01:23:49,520
To check that his records
office is fully operational,

994
01:23:49,563 --> 01:23:53,147
he wanted to see if it is possible
to locate a particular individual.

995
01:23:53,193 --> 01:23:55,945
A fascinating exercise,
I'm sure you'll agree.

996
01:23:57,657 --> 01:24:02,404
The name, selected at
random, is Gluckstein.

997
01:24:03,956 --> 01:24:06,163
Maurice Gluckstein.

998
01:24:06,209 --> 01:24:10,078
Our records show that he
should be here somewhere.

999
01:24:10,131 --> 01:24:15,589
Sorry to disappoint you, Professor, but at any
given time we've got up to 30,000 items here.

1000
01:24:15,638 --> 01:24:18,309
And the turnover is considerable.

1001
01:24:18,351 --> 01:24:21,388
Moreover, on arrival, each
item is allocated a number,

1002
01:24:21,438 --> 01:24:24,310
which becomes its sole
means of identification.

1003
01:24:24,359 --> 01:24:28,108
So all we have to do is
find Gluckstein's number?

1004
01:24:28,155 --> 01:24:31,110
- In theory, yes.
- But?

1005
01:24:32,244 --> 01:24:34,118
Let me put it this way, Professor,

1006
01:24:34,163 --> 01:24:38,625
I'm sure from Head Office
everything looks neat and tidy,

1007
01:24:38,668 --> 01:24:41,374
- but out here...
- Can you find this man or not?

1008
01:24:41,422 --> 01:24:44,092
Frankly, not a chance in hell.

1009
01:24:44,927 --> 01:24:47,383
Nine out of ten are
processed on arrival.

1010
01:24:47,430 --> 01:24:50,052
No one is here for more
than a month or two.

1011
01:24:53,270 --> 01:24:54,730
Isee.

1012
01:25:04,744 --> 01:25:06,120
Stop!

1013
01:25:20,807 --> 01:25:22,087
Move!

1014
01:25:28,525 --> 01:25:30,399
Come on!

1015
01:25:39,164 --> 01:25:41,241
Keep moving!

1016
01:29:13,276 --> 01:29:14,936
It's real.

1017
01:29:47,320 --> 01:29:49,479
Move it! Come on, there!

